Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a perhaps Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine ginger-buff. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 121, 1? From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX TAL098.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1603)
